# INSTALLATION 

The PIC pipeline has been tested on a Linux Fedora 7.2 ('Nitrogen')

Follow the instructions from the manuals to install the following items:

	* bowtie: http://bowtie-bio.sourceforge.net/tutorial.shtml (≥1.1.2)
	* bowtie2: http://bowtie-bio.sourceforge.net/bowtie2/index.shtml (≥2.2.9)
	* cutadapt: https://cutadapt.readthedocs.io/en/stable/installation.html (≥1.7.1)
	* fastx: http://hannonlab.cshl.edu/fastx_toolkit/ (≥0.0.13)
	* samtools: http://samtools.sourceforge.net/ (≥0.1.19)

R can be obtained here: https://www.r-project.org/

## Installing R packages

A) PIC package is not currently inside any R package repository and has to be installed by the following shell command line:

	R CMD INSTALL path/to/PIC_1.3.tar.gz

B) The following R packages can be installed using R install.packages("package_name")

	* dplyr (≥0.7.6)
	* ggplot2 (≥2.2.1)
	* tibble (≥1.4.2)
	* readr (≥1.1.1)
	* WriteXLS (≥4.0.0)
	* stringr (≥1.3)
	* tidyr (≥0.8)

C) The last two R packages require Bioconductor (https://bioconductor.org/)

  1) Install R Bioconductor:

	https://bioconductor.org/install/

  2) Install R Bioconductor packages using BiocManager::install("package_name")

  	* ShortRead (≥1.3)
  	* GenomicRanges (≥1.32.2)
	* Rsamtools (≥1.34.1)
